After a meeting with local scientists, South Africa's health ministry reported that 22 women in recent trials for an HIV prevention gel contracted the virus.
Despite setbacks, ongoing ethical trials for microbicides offer hope in preventing HIV infections.
The Lancet published results showing male circumcision reduces HIV risk by over half, validating calls for its use in AIDS prevention.
Studies on anti-AIDS vaginal gels have faced challenges, while research on treating herpes to slow HIV transmission shows promise.
Efforts to combat HIV/AIDS in Africa include increasing access to basic healthcare and addressing social issues.
